life was like back then?

187
00:09:29.504 --> 00:09:31.670
<i>I worked for</i>
<i>a family.</i>

188
00:09:31.672 --> 00:09:34.507
<i>Housework. cleaning.</i>
<i>looking after their kid.</i>

189
00:09:34.509 --> 00:09:37.576
<i>Nice people.</i>
<i>but a bit well-to-do.</i>

190
00:09:37.578 --> 00:09:39.211
<i>-You know the sort.</i>
-Sure.

191
00:09:39.213 --> 00:09:41.480
<i>But good employers.</i>

192
00:09:41.482 --> 00:09:42.981
<i>They were even</i>
<i>paying to put my girl</i>

193
00:09:42.983 --> 00:09:45.617
<i>on a scholarship</i>
<i>to a good school.</i>

194
00:09:45.619 --> 00:09:48.220
<i>They treated her like</i>
<i>she was their own daughter.</i>

195
00:09:48.222 --> 00:09:52.224
<i>We were so grateful for</i>
<i>everything they gave us.</i>

196
00:09:52.226 --> 00:09:55.194
But something went wrong?

197
00:09:55.196 --> 00:09:57.863
<i>One day. something</i>
<i>happened in the house that</i>

198
00:09:57.865 --> 00:09:59.431
<i>I still can't</i>
<i>explain.</i>

199
00:09:59.433 --> 00:10:01.000
What do you mean?

200
00:10:02.837 --> 00:10:04.637
<i>I don't know</i>
<i>if I can say it.</i>

201
00:10:06.006 --> 00:10:08.340
I'm not here to judge you.
Floramae.

202
00:10:08.342 --> 00:10:10.143
I just wanna listen.

203
00:10:12.113 --> 00:10:14.913
<i>Well. one day.</i>
<i>I came in to find</i>

204
00:10:14.915 --> 00:10:17.116
<i>all this terrible</i>
<i>damage to their furniture.</i>

205
00:10:17.118 --> 00:10:19.718
<i>Big. awful scratches</i>
<i>across everything.</i>

206
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:21.753
<i>The dining table</i>
<i>was the worst.</i>

207
00:10:21.755 --> 00:10:24.089
<i>It was like</i>
<i>somebody was so angry.</i>

208
00:10:24.091 --> 00:10:25.724
<i>they grabbed the</i>
<i>sharpest knife they could</i>
<i>find</i>

209
00:10:25.726 --> 00:10:28.660
<i>and stabbed and</i>
<i>stabbed at the table.</i>

210
00:10:28.662 --> 00:10:31.396
<i>making these big.</i>
<i>deep scratches.</i>

211
00:10:31.398 --> 00:10:33.765
Sounds really frightening.

212
00:10:33.767 --> 00:10:37.604
<i>It was. but...</i>
<i>but it got worse.</i>

213
00:10:37.606 --> 00:10:40.072
<i>The family thought that</i>
<i>my girl Paula had done it.</i>

214
00:10:40.074 --> 00:10:42.741
<i>She was only a kid</i>

215
00:10:42.743 --> 00:10:44.776
<i>and she swore black</i>
<i>and blue she didn't.</i>

216
00:10:44.778 --> 00:10:47.679
<i>but they didn't</i>
<i>believe her.</i>

217
00:10:47.681 --> 00:10:49.415
Did you think she did it?

218
00:10:51.252 --> 00:10:52.719
<i>It makes</i>
<i>me ashamed.</i>

219
00:10:54.021 --> 00:10:56.955
<i>Paula never</i>
<i>admitted it.</i>

220
00:10:56.957 --> 00:10:59.791
[exhales shakily] <i>There</i>
<i>was a lot of pressure.</i>

221
00:10:59.793 --> 00:11:02.427
<i>and I didn't feel that</i>
<i>I could stand up to them.</i>

222
00:11:02.429 --> 00:11:05.797
<i>I didn't</i>
<i>believe her.</i>

223
00:11:05.799 --> 00:11:08.234
<i>Over the years.</i>
<i>I've always wondered...</i>

224
00:11:10.905 --> 00:11:14.040
If she didn't destroy
the furniture. who did?

225
00:11:14.708 --> 00:11:17.610
<i>Exactly.</i>

226
00:11:17.612 --> 00:11:19.845
<i>It caused big</i>
<i>trouble in the house.</i>

227
00:11:19.847 --> 00:11:21.446
<i>and the family</i>
<i>turned on us.</i>

228
00:11:21.448 --> 00:11:24.082
<i>turned on Paula.</i>

229
00:11:24.084 --> 00:11:26.251
<i>And I couldn't</i>
<i>do anything to stop it.</i>

230
00:11:26.253 --> 00:11:28.687
<i>I couldn't help</i>
<i>my little girl. and...</i>

231
00:11:28.689 --> 00:11:30.590
<i>I was such</i>
<i>a terrible mother. and...</i>

232
00:11:30.592 --> 00:11:34.126
[Floramae sighs]

233
00:11:34.128 --> 00:11:37.296
<i>And that's when I</i>
<i>received the strangest</i>
<i>thing.</i>

234
00:11:37.298 --> 00:11:40.966
<i>This black brick.</i>

235
00:11:40.968 --> 00:11:43.302
What do you mean.
received it?

236
00:11:43.304 --> 00:11:45.370
How?

237
00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:48.340
[Floramae exclaims]

238
00:11:48.342 --> 00:11:49.542
<i>I--I don't</i>
<i>remember.</i>

239
00:11:49.544 --> 00:11:51.877
You don't remember?

240
00:11:51.879 --> 00:11:54.514
<i>It was a long</i>
<i>time ago.</i>

241
00:11:54.516 --> 00:11:56.649
It's okay.

242
00:11:56.651 --> 00:11:59.986
Can you tell me
what the brick was like?

243
00:12:02.557 --> 00:12:04.156
<i>It was darker than</i>
<i>anything I've ever seen</i>

244
00:12:04.158 --> 00:12:06.826
<i>and heavy.</i>

245
00:12:07.728 --> 00:12:10.028
<i>It was special.</i>

246
00:12:10.030 --> 00:12:11.997
<i>As soon as I held</i>
<i>it. I felt like</i>

247
00:12:11.999 --> 00:12:14.367
<i>something</i>
<i>was changing.</i>

248
00:12:16.136 --> 00:12:17.937
<i>But then...</i>

249
00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:20.840
What happened?

250
00:12:22.611 --> 00:12:24.711
<i>The couple I</i>
<i>was working for.</i>

251
00:12:24.713 --> 00:12:27.012
<i>their kid took</i>
<i>it from me.</i>

252
00:12:27.014 --> 00:12:28.914
<i>And when the</i>
<i>husband saw it.</i>

253
00:12:28.916 --> 00:12:30.782
<i>he thought he could</i>
<i>make some money.</i>

254
00:12:30.784 --> 00:12:33.252
<i>He told me</i>
<i>it was art.</i>

255
00:12:33.254 --> 00:12:35.187
<i>I'll never forgive</i>
<i>him for selling it.</i>

256
00:12:35.189 --> 00:12:37.956
He sold it
without your permission?

257
00:12:37.958 --> 00:12:40.058
<i>After they decided my</i>
<i>Paula ruined their</i>
<i>furniture.</i>

258
00:12:40.060 --> 00:12:42.294
<i>we had to pay</i>
<i>for the damage.</i>

259
00:12:42.296 --> 00:12:44.930
<i>So they took the brick</i>
<i>as part of the payment.</i>

260
00:12:44.932 --> 00:12:46.699
<i>It makes me wild.</i>

261
00:12:46.701 --> 00:12:48.800
Who'd he sell it to?

262
00:12:48.802 --> 00:12:51.470
<i>Some art collector.</i>

263
00:12:51.472 --> 00:12:53.640
Do you remember a name?

264
00:12:53.642 --> 00:12:58.176
<i>Something German.</i>
<i>Lang. maybe?</i>

265
00:12:58.178 --> 00:13:00.647
That must've made you feel
really awful.

266
00:13:00.649 --> 00:13:02.749
<i>-I tried to stop</i>
<i>it.</i> -Mm.

267
00:13:02.751 --> 00:13:04.883
<i>I told the couple</i>
<i>that that brick was mine.</i>

268
00:13:04.885 --> 00:13:06.852
<i>You know.</i>
<i>people can't go around</i>

269
00:13:06.854 --> 00:13:08.920
<i>selling what's not</i>
<i>theirs. can they?</i>

270
00:13:08.922 --> 00:13:11.089
<i>But as soon as the</i>
<i>family found out</i>

271
00:13:11.091 --> 00:13:13.660
<i>I wanted to go</i>
<i>to the authorities.</i>

272
00:13:13.662 --> 00:13:16.295
<i>they removed me.</i>

273
00:13:16.297 --> 00:13:17.863
They fired you.

274
00:13:17.865 --> 00:13:20.533
<i>Easy as you please.</i>

275
00:13:20.535 --> 00:13:22.902
<i>Years of</i>
<i>service gone.</i>

276
00:13:24.238 --> 00:13:25.938
<i>I never heard</i>
<i>from them again.</i>

277
00:13:27.174 --> 00:13:30.042
<i>I never saw the</i>
<i>brick again.</i>

278
00:13:30.044 --> 00:13:33.680
What do you think
this brick was. Floramae?

279
00:13:33.682 --> 00:13:35.881
[exhales]
<i>I'm not sure.</i>

280
00:13:35.883 --> 00:13:38.317
<i>Maybe nothing.</i>

281
00:13:38.319 --> 00:13:39.786
Somebody thought it was
interesting enough

282
00:13:39.788 --> 00:13:43.155
to email me about.

283
00:13:43.157 --> 00:13:47.359
And you say
the brick was special. right?

284
00:13:47.361 --> 00:13:49.127
What'd it make you feel?

285
00:13:49.129 --> 00:13:52.197
[unsettling music playing]

286
00:13:52.199 --> 00:13:54.600
<i>Sometimes. I think</i>
<i>I can still feel it.</i>

287
00:13:54.602 --> 00:13:57.102
<i>That power.</i>

288
00:13:57.104 --> 00:14:01.406
<i>like something</i>
<i>unfinished.</i>

289
00:14:01.408 --> 00:14:03.442
<i>I can't explain it.</i>

290
00:14:03.444 --> 00:14:05.778
<i>I don't know.</i>

291
00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:09.181
<i>This was 20 years</i>
<i>ago. it's silly.</i>

292
00:14:09.183 --> 00:14:12.951
<i>I thought that there</i>
<i>was some kind of power over</i>
<i>me.</i>

293
00:14:12.953 --> 00:14:15.220
<i>Yeah. it was probably</i>
<i>all in my head.</i>

294
00:14:15.222 --> 00:14:17.155
<i>Sorry if this</i>
<i>is a dead-end.</i>

295
00:14:17.157 --> 00:14:20.158
It's okay.

296
00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:21.828
Maybe there's something
that will jog your memory. We
can--

297
00:14:21.830 --> 00:14:24.196
[Paula] <i>Mom. come on.</i>
<i>lunch is just sitting.</i>

298
00:14:24.198 --> 00:14:25.765
<i>-I know. it's getting</i>
<i>cold.</i> -[Paula] <i>Who is</i>
<i>that?</i>

299
00:14:25.767 --> 00:14:27.065
[Floramae] <i>I'll pop it</i>
<i>in the microwave. hon.</i>

300
00:14:27.067 --> 00:14:27.800
<i>-Give it to me.</i>
<i>-Hang on a tick.</i>

301
00:14:27.802 --> 00:14:29.434
<i>Hang on. Paula.</i>

302
00:14:29.436 --> 00:14:31.870
<i>Hello. who is this?</i>

303
00:14:31.872 --> 00:14:34.005
Sorry. I was speaking
with Floramae--

304
00:14:34.007 --> 00:14:37.042
<i>Whatever you're</i>
<i>selling. leave Mom alone.</i>

305
00:14:37.044 --> 00:14:39.010
<i>-Paula! You don't--</i>
<i>-People need to stop</i>
<i>calling.</i>

306
00:14:39.012 --> 00:14:42.114
<i>She doesn't need any</i>
<i>more crap in her house.</i>

307
00:14:42.116 --> 00:14:45.283
-No. of course. -[Paula]
<i>Sorry. it's just...</i>

308
00:14:45.285 --> 00:14:46.853
<i>-You understand.</i>
<i>right?</i> -[Floramae] <i>Hang</i>
<i>on. Paula!</i>

309
00:14:46.855 --> 00:14:50.590
[beeping as call
disconnects]

310
00:14:50.592 --> 00:14:52.392
[exhales sharply]

311
00:14:52.727 --> 00:14:54.960
[sighs]

312
00:14:54.962 --> 00:14:57.262
[man] <i>Godmorgen.</i>
<i>mit barn.</i>

313
00:14:57.264 --> 00:14:58.897
<i>Just calling to let you</i>
<i>know we've made it to...</i>

314
00:14:58.899 --> 00:15:01.768
[man and woman together]
<i>Beautiful Copenhagen!</i>

315
00:15:01.770 --> 00:15:04.537
[man] <i>We're alive and</i>
<i>well in our very lovely</i>
<i>hotel.</i>

316
00:15:04.539 --> 00:15:07.406
[woman] <i>Why do the</i>
<i>Danes have to pickle</i>
<i>everything?</i>

317
00:15:07.408 --> 00:15:09.542
[dad] <i>And your mother's</i>
<i>already complaining about all</i>
<i>the fish.</i>

318
00:15:09.544 --> 00:15:11.109
[mom] <i>Darling. we can</i>
<i>get you a new jacket. if you</i>
<i>like.</i>

319
00:15:11.111 --> 00:15:13.078
[dad] <i>She doesn't</i>
<i>want a jacket.</i>

320
00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:14.980
[mom] <i>Don't be stupid.</i>
<i>of course she does.</i>

321
00:15:14.982 --> 00:15:15.882
[dad] <i>There's some</i>
<i>leftovers in the freezer.</i>

322
00:15:15.884 --> 00:15:17.249
[mom] <i>And</i>
<i>don't forget.</i>

323
00:15:17.251 --> 00:15:18.684
<i>Ian's tank needs</i>
<i>to be cleaned</i>

324
00:15:18.686 --> 00:15:21.153
<i>-twice a week.</i>
-[dad laughs]

325
00:15:21.155 --> 00:15:25.490
<i>We heard about the new</i>
<i>podcast. Sounds interesting.</i>

326
00:15:25.492 --> 00:15:27.760
<i>Good little diversion</i>
<i>after everything that's</i>
<i>happened.</i>

327
00:15:27.762 --> 00:15:29.361
<i>Obviously. those</i>
<i>bastards at The Evening</i>
<i>Journal</i>

328
00:15:29.363 --> 00:15:31.864
<i>had no right to</i>
<i>scapegoat you like that.</i>

329
00:15:31.866 --> 00:15:33.398
<i>You know you did the</i>
<i>right thing with Langley</i>

330
00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:34.500
<i>and you've got</i>
<i>nothing to apologize--</i>

331
00:15:34.502 --> 00:15:36.002
[stops voicemail playback]

332
00:15:37.171 --> 00:15:39.971
[telephone ringing]

333
00:15:39.973 --> 00:15:42.642
[bubbling]

334
00:15:42.644 --> 00:15:47.179
[telephone ringing]

335
00:15:47.181 --> 00:15:49.414
<i>Lang Contemporary.</i>
<i>Frau Schmidt. Guten tag.</i>

336
00:15:49.416 --> 00:15:50.982
[stammers] Hallo.

337
00:15:50.984 --> 00:15:54.620
kann ich bitte
mit Klaus Lang sprechen?

338
00:15:54.622 --> 00:15:56.955
-Sorry.
<i>-Of course.</i>

339
00:15:56.957 --> 00:15:58.724
<i>May I ask</i>
<i>why you are calling?</i>

340
00:15:58.726 --> 00:16:03.495
[hold music plays]

341
00:16:03.497 --> 00:16:05.397
[Klaus] <i>I never thought</i>
<i>I would get a call</i>

342
00:16:05.399 --> 00:16:06.833
<i>about these funny</i>
<i>little objects of mine.</i>

343
00:16:06.835 --> 00:16:10.335
Hi. Mr. Lang.

344
00:16:10.337 --> 00:16:14.372
I. uh. work for a podcast
called Beyond Believable.

345
00:16:14.374 --> 00:16:17.944
It's about unsolved
mysteries. hoaxes. that kind of
thing.

346
00:16:17.946 --> 00:16:22.515
I. uh. came across a story
about a black brick

347
00:16:22.517 --> 00:16:26.017
that you bought from an
Australian man many years ago.

348
00:16:26.019 --> 00:16:29.889
and I just wanna
corroborate a few details with
you.

349
00:16:29.891 --> 00:16:32.558
<i>Most curious. A hoax?</i>
<i>I'm not so sure.</i>

350
00:16:32.560 --> 00:16:34.727
Before we go any further.

351
00:16:34.729 --> 00:16:36.394
I'm letting you know
I'm recording our conversation

352
00:16:36.396 --> 00:16:37.763
for the podcast.

353
00:16:37.765 --> 00:16:39.665
Do you mind?

354
00:16:39.667 --> 00:16:42.568
<i>You're already</i>
<i>recording?</i>

355
00:16:42.570 --> 00:16:44.035
I've found it's always
better to ask for forgiveness

356
00:16:44.037 --> 00:16:45.538
than permission.

357
00:16:45.540 --> 00:16:47.807
[Klaus laughs]

358
00:16:47.809 --> 00:16:50.308
<i>I agree entirely.</i>
<i>Go ahead.</i>

359
00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:54.814
So you're telling me
this object really exists?

360
00:16:54.816 --> 00:16:58.183
<i>Yes. yes. in fact.</i>
<i>I have several.</i>

361
00:16:58.185 --> 00:17:00.352
What do you mean. several?

362
00:17:00.354 --> 00:17:02.020
<i>See. I am also</i>
<i>very interested</i>

363
00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:04.356
<i>in this phenomenon.</i>

364
00:17:04.358 --> 00:17:06.258
<i>When I was a</i>
<i>very young man.</i>

365
00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:09.027
<i>I also received</i>
<i>a brick.</i>

366
00:17:09.029 --> 00:17:10.930
You're kidding me.

367
00:17:10.932 --> 00:17:13.465
<i>Not at all.</i>
<i>not at all.</i>

368
00:17:13.467 --> 00:17:17.235
<i>And I've been</i>
<i>fascinated with them ever</i>
<i>since.</i>

369
00:17:17.237 --> 00:17:18.336
So you're saying
there's more than one

370
00:17:18.338 --> 00:17:20.673
of these objects
out there.

371
00:17:20.675 --> 00:17:22.775
<i>I know of at least a</i>
<i>dozen around the world.</i>

372
00:17:22.777 --> 00:17:25.310
<i>of which I</i>
<i>have a few.</i>

373
00:17:25.312 --> 00:17:27.914
<i>each exactly</i>
<i>the same.</i>

374
00:17:27.916 --> 00:17:29.783
<i>Most peculiar.</i>
<i>Very collectible.</i>

375
00:17:31.986 --> 00:17:35.756
And how did you receive
your brick. Mr. Lang?

376
00:17:37.457 --> 00:17:42.193
<i>It was. uh. just.</i>
<i>uh. in my house.</i>

377
00:17:42.195 --> 00:17:45.598
Can you. uh.
can you describe these bricks?

378
00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:47.967
<i>They are black.</i>

379
00:17:47.969 --> 00:17:50.402
<i>About the size</i>
<i>of a gold bar.</i>

380
00:17:50.404 --> 00:17:54.507
<i>but darker than any</i>
<i>other object I have seen.</i>

381
00:17:54.509 --> 00:17:58.243
<i>Very heavy. not</i>
<i>manmade. but not natural</i>
<i>either.</i>

382
00:17:58.245 --> 00:18:00.680
It's either one
or the other. no?

383
00:18:00.682 --> 00:18:02.080
<i>I thought</i>
<i>like this.</i>

384
00:18:02.082 --> 00:18:04.249
<i>So several</i>
<i>years ago.</i>

385
00:18:04.251 --> 00:18:06.484
<i>I took these artifacts</i>
<i>to a friend of mine.</i>

386
00:18:06.486 --> 00:18:10.255
<i>and she made scans</i>
<i>with the new technology.</i>

387
00:18:10.257 --> 00:18:12.558
<i>They call it</i>
<i>volumetric scanning.</i>

388
00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:14.894
<i>You can make</i>
<i>a three-dimensional image</i>

389
00:18:14.896 --> 00:18:17.128
<i>of the interior</i>
<i>without opening it up.</i>

390
00:18:17.130 --> 00:18:19.966
<i>-Very cool. huh?</i>
-And?

391
00:18:19.968 --> 00:18:22.200
<i>I have never seen</i>
<i>anything like it.</i>

392
00:18:22.202 --> 00:18:24.269
<i>Uh. the interior</i>
<i>of each brick</i>

393
00:18:24.271 --> 00:18:26.371
<i>is filled</i>
<i>with hundreds of symbols</i>

394
00:18:26.373 --> 00:18:28.007
<i>folded into</i>
<i>each other.</i>

395
00:18:28.009 --> 00:18:30.108
Can you send
me these scans?

396
00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:32.979
<i>It was years ago.</i>

397
00:18:32.981 --> 00:18:34.714
<i>I'll see if I</i>
<i>can dig them up.</i>

398
00:18:34.716 --> 00:18:38.483
<i>Perhaps you can make</i>
<i>something of them.</i>

399
00:18:38.485 --> 00:18:42.088
And these symbols...
what alphabet is it?

400
00:18:42.090 --> 00:18:46.391
Latin. Arabic. Cyrillic.
hieroglyphic?

401
00:18:46.393 --> 00:18:50.195
<i>Each brick has its own</i>
<i>unique set of symbols.</i>

402
00:18:50.197 --> 00:18:53.666
<i>But in mine. I see a</i>
<i>symbol that reminds me of a</i>
<i>scar</i>

403
00:18:53.668 --> 00:18:57.268
<i>that I have had</i>
<i>since I was a small boy.</i>

404
00:18:57.270 --> 00:19:01.608
<i>It makes me think this</i>
<i>brick is speaking directly to</i>
<i>me.</i>

405
00:19:03.143 --> 00:19:05.978
What do you mean?

406
00:19:05.980 --> 00:19:09.147
<i>Well. you see.</i>
<i>uh...</i> [laughs]

407
00:19:09.149 --> 00:19:11.117
<i>You probably</i>
<i>think I'm crazy.</i>

408
00:19:11.119 --> 00:19:14.419
No. G-go on. please.

409
00:19:14.421 --> 00:19:18.624
<i>For a while. I thought</i>
<i>I was completely verruckt.</i>

410
00:19:18.626 --> 00:19:19.759
<i>crazy as a cuckoo.</i>

411
00:19:19.761 --> 00:19:23.161
[laughter]

412
00:19:23.163 --> 00:19:25.998
<i>Many...many</i>
<i>years ago.</i>

413
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:28.166
<i>just before</i>
<i>I received my brick.</i>

414
00:19:28.168 --> 00:19:30.736
<i>I-I had a very strange.</i>
<i>uh. what do you call it.</i>

415
00:19:30.738 --> 00:19:32.972
<i>like a-- like a dream</i>
<i>when you are awake.</i>

416
00:19:32.974 --> 00:19:35.741
Uh. daydream?

417
00:19:35.743 --> 00:19:39.078
<i>Yeah. but it</i>
<i>felt real.</i>

418
00:19:39.080 --> 00:19:41.714
<i>A vision.</i>

419
00:19:41.716 --> 00:19:45.084
<i>This awful creature</i>
<i>appeared in my bathroom.</i>

420
00:19:45.086 --> 00:19:46.952
Sorry. did you--
a creature?

421
00:19:46.954 --> 00:19:49.889
[unsettling music playing]

422
00:19:49.891 --> 00:19:51.957
<i>It was a man.</i>

423
00:19:51.959 --> 00:19:56.428
<i>but grotesque.</i>
<i>awful.</i>

424
00:19:56.430 --> 00:20:00.298
<i>A face like</i>
<i>wet bread.</i>

425
00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:03.769
<i>And it was most</i>
<i>extraordinary. but somehow.</i>

426
00:20:03.771 --> 00:20:08.140
<i>I knew this creature</i>
<i>was my brother.</i>

427
00:20:08.142 --> 00:20:10.475
<i>An awful. ugly</i>
<i>version of him.</i>

428
00:20:10.477 --> 00:20:14.379
<i>this thing</i>
<i>would never say a word.</i>

429
00:20:14.381 --> 00:20:17.850
<i>But I knew it was my</i>
<i>brother all the same.</i>

430
00:20:17.852 --> 00:20:20.285
How?

431
00:20:20.287 --> 00:20:23.455
<i>A feeling.</i>

432
00:20:23.457 --> 00:20:25.423
<i>It was connected</i>
<i>to me and I to it.</i>

433
00:20:25.425 --> 00:20:28.326
[unsettling
music continues]

434
00:20:28.328 --> 00:20:30.361
<i>My brother was a</i>
<i>teenager when he died.</i>

435
00:20:30.363 --> 00:20:33.065
<i>He had a bad heart.</i>

436
00:20:33.067 --> 00:20:36.802
<i>Time was always</i>
<i>against us.</i>

437
00:20:36.804 --> 00:20:41.140
<i>That creature in my</i>
<i>bathtub watching me.</i>

438
00:20:41.142 --> 00:20:43.610
<i>telling me</i>
<i>what I have always known.</i>

439
00:20:49.016 --> 00:20:50.784
Which is?

440
00:20:53.286 --> 00:20:55.655
<i>A part of me</i>
<i>wanted him to die.</i>

441
00:20:59.093 --> 00:21:04.897
<i>He was so clever</i>
<i>and strong and loved.</i>

442
00:21:04.899 --> 00:21:07.332
<i>I could never</i>
<i>compete.</i>

443
00:21:07.334 --> 00:21:08.768
<i>But then. he died.</i>

444
00:21:08.770 --> 00:21:11.103
<i>I felt...</i>

445
00:21:11.105 --> 00:21:13.038
<i>happy.</i>

446
00:21:13.040 --> 00:21:15.008
<i>Relieved.</i>

447
00:21:17.645 --> 00:21:21.379
[Klaus sighs] <i>And after</i>
<i>this terrible vision.</i>

448
00:21:21.381 --> 00:21:24.918
<i>that's when</i>
<i>I received the brick.</i>

449
00:21:27.021 --> 00:21:29.454
But this vision was
just your imagination. right?

450
00:21:29.456 --> 00:21:32.758
It wasn't actually real.

451
00:21:32.760 --> 00:21:35.161
<i>The logical thinking</i>
<i>part of my brain knew it wasn't</i>
<i>real.</i>

452
00:21:35.163 --> 00:21:38.496
<i>but in my heart.</i>
<i>it felt differently.</i>

453
00:21:38.498 --> 00:21:43.068
<i>It was like</i>
<i>a hallucination.</i>

454
00:21:43.070 --> 00:21:45.805
<i>Even after I locked the</i>
<i>brick away all those years</i>
<i>ago.</i>

455
00:21:45.807 --> 00:21:48.040
<i>it still haunts me.</i>

456
00:21:48.042 --> 00:21:52.377
<i>A little less.</i>
<i>but it's there.</i>

457
00:21:52.379 --> 00:21:54.880
What makes you think
you're not crazy. Mr. Lang?

458
00:21:54.882 --> 00:21:57.448
[Klaus laughs]

459
00:21:57.450 --> 00:21:59.952
<i>You're right. yeah.</i>

460
00:21:59.954 --> 00:22:01.452
<i>A madman never</i>
<i>thinks he's mad.</i>

461
00:22:01.454 --> 00:22:02.988
[Klaus laughs]

462
00:22:02.990 --> 00:22:05.356
<i>But I am normally</i>

463
00:22:05.358 --> 00:22:07.226
<i>a very straight-ahead</i>
<i>kind of guy.</i>

464
00:22:07.228 --> 00:22:08.994
<i>No drink. no drugs.</i>

465
00:22:08.996 --> 00:22:10.196
<i>I like reality</i>
<i>very much.</i>

466
00:22:10.198 --> 00:22:12.965
[Klaus laughs]

467
00:22:12.967 --> 00:22:16.268
And you think this vision
is connected to the brick?

468
00:22:16.270 --> 00:22:18.003
<i>I'm certain of it.</i>

469
00:22:18.005 --> 00:22:21.140
[unsettling music playing]

470
00:22:21.142 --> 00:22:22.241
<i>You don't</i>
<i>believe me.</i>

471
00:22:22.243 --> 00:22:24.476
[laughs]

472
00:22:25.646 --> 00:22:28.747
-No.
<i>-Okay. Very good.</i>

473
00:22:28.749 --> 00:22:31.317
<i>You are an investigator</i>
<i>of the facts.</i>

474
00:22:31.319 --> 00:22:33.620
<i>not some silly</i>
<i>conspiracy cuckoo.</i>

475
00:22:34.856 --> 00:22:36.522
<i>But know this:</i>

476
00:22:36.524 --> 00:22:38.858
<i>I am a good man.</i>

477
00:22:38.860 --> 00:22:41.492
<i>I do believe in the</i>
<i>truth. in facts.</i>

478
00:22:41.494 --> 00:22:43.295
<i>and when I held</i>
<i>this brick.</i>

479
00:22:43.297 --> 00:22:46.665
<i>it felt like</i>
<i>something or someone</i>

480
00:22:46.667 --> 00:22:48.702
<i>was trying to</i>
<i>talk to me.</i>

481
00:22:50.238 --> 00:22:52.939
<i>A message</i>
<i>from far away.</i>

482
00:22:54.374 --> 00:22:58.644
Are you saying you think
this brick is alien?

483
00:22:58.646 --> 00:23:01.580
<i>If you don't believe</i>
<i>me. I am happy to send you a</i>
<i>brick.</i>

484
00:23:01.582 --> 00:23:05.651
-Really?
<i>-Ja. For a small fee.</i>

485
00:23:05.653 --> 00:23:07.553
[laughs] You're
selling them.

486
00:23:07.555 --> 00:23:09.755
<i>Of course!</i>
<i>Of course.</i>

487
00:23:09.757 --> 00:23:12.224
<i>I'm a businessman.</i>
<i>after all.</i>

488
00:23:12.226 --> 00:23:13.592
<i>I am willing to</i>
<i>offer a good deal</i>

489
00:23:13.594 --> 00:23:15.628
<i>to a smart</i>
<i>girl like you.</i>

490
00:23:15.630 --> 00:23:19.531
Well. thank you. but. uh.

491
00:23:19.533 --> 00:23:21.267
I think I have
everything I need.

492
00:23:21.269 --> 00:23:24.270
<i>Very well.</i>

493
00:23:24.272 --> 00:23:26.972
<i>I hope you find</i>
<i>what you're looking for.</i>

494
00:23:26.974 --> 00:23:29.241
[pensive music playing]

495
00:23:29.243 --> 00:23:31.343
Mr. Lang. just...

496
00:23:31.345 --> 00:23:34.445
-Just one more thing.
<i>-Ja.</i>

497
00:23:34.447 --> 00:23:36.248
That brick from Australia.
the man you bought it from

498
00:23:36.250 --> 00:23:38.784
sold it without
permission.

499
00:23:38.786 --> 00:23:41.086
It was his housekeeper's.
originally.

500
00:23:41.088 --> 00:23:42.789
Did you know that?

501
00:23:45.526 --> 00:23:48.227
<i>Throw a rock and you</i>
<i>will hit a gallery</i>

502
00:23:48.229 --> 00:23:51.330
<i>filled with</i>
<i>stolen artwork.</i>

503
00:23:51.332 --> 00:23:53.999
<i>It was once</i>
<i>a German pastime.</i>

504
00:23:54.001 --> 00:23:55.401
I'm sure it's challenging
to remain ethical

505
00:23:55.403 --> 00:23:58.671
in your industry.

506
00:23:58.673 --> 00:24:00.639
<i>I really am</i>
<i>quite busy.</i>

507
00:24:00.641 --> 00:24:02.473
<i>so if you have</i>
<i>nothing else you need...</i>

508
00:24:02.475 --> 00:24:05.778
Yes. thank you. um...

509
00:24:05.780 --> 00:24:07.046
thank you for your time.
Mr. Lang.

510
00:24:07.048 --> 00:24:08.881
<i>Guten tag.</i>

511
00:24:08.883 --> 00:24:11.317
[distant thunder]

512
00:24:11.319 --> 00:24:15.087
[unsettling music playing]

513
00:24:15.089 --> 00:24:18.624
[interviewer] <i>So you're</i>
<i>telling me this object really</i>
<i>exists?</i>

514
00:24:18.626 --> 00:24:19.992
[Floramae] <i>It was like</i>
<i>nothing I'd ever seen.</i>

515
00:24:19.994 --> 00:24:22.962
<i>It changed my life.</i>

516
00:24:22.964 --> 00:24:24.830
[Klaus] <i>I never thought</i>
<i>I would get a call</i>

517
00:24:24.832 --> 00:24:27.533
<i>about these funny</i>
<i>little objects of mine.</i>

518
00:24:27.535 --> 00:24:29.335
[Floramae] <i>That's when</i>
<i>I received the strangest</i>
<i>thing.</i>

519
00:24:29.337 --> 00:24:31.637
<i>this black brick.</i>

520
00:24:31.639 --> 00:24:33.672
[Klaus] <i>About the</i>
<i>size of a gold bar.</i>

521
00:24:33.674 --> 00:24:35.841
<i>darker than any other</i>
<i>object I have seen.</i>

522
00:24:35.843 --> 00:24:38.077
[voice speeds
up. distorts]

523
00:24:38.079 --> 00:24:39.912
[interviewer] <i>How did</i>
<i>you receive your brick?</i>

524
00:24:39.914 --> 00:24:42.648
[Klaus laughs] <i>You</i>
<i>probably think I'm crazy.</i>

525
00:24:42.650 --> 00:24:44.450
[Floramae] <i>The brick</i>
<i>was such a long time ago.</i>

526
00:24:44.452 --> 00:24:46.852
[Klaus] <i>It felt like</i>
<i>something or someone</i>

527
00:24:46.854 --> 00:24:48.587
<i>was trying to</i>
<i>talk to me.</i>

528
00:24:48.589 --> 00:24:50.990
[Floramae's voice
speeds up. distorts]

529
00:24:50.992 --> 00:24:52.624
<i>I thought that there</i>
<i>was some kind of power over</i>
<i>me.</i>

530
00:24:52.626 --> 00:24:55.861
[Klaus] <i>A message</i>
<i>from far away.</i>

531
00:24:55.863 --> 00:24:56.462
[Floramae] <i>Yeah. it was</i>
<i>probably all in my head.</i>

532
00:24:56.464 --> 00:24:59.531
[sighs]

533
00:24:59.533 --> 00:25:01.867
[man laughs] <i>Come on.</i>
<i>it can't be that bad.</i>

534
00:25:01.869 --> 00:25:05.037
[interviewer] Honestly.
it's bad. Scott.

535
00:25:05.039 --> 00:25:09.742
Anonymous emails and
visions and weird scratchings.

536
00:25:09.744 --> 00:25:11.744
Oh. and let's not forget
the brick.

537
00:25:11.746 --> 00:25:15.547
I mean. come on.
it's ridiculous.

538
00:25:15.549 --> 00:25:18.183
-A brick.
-[Scott laughs]

539
00:25:18.185 --> 00:25:19.651
Even the woman
says it herself.

540
00:25:19.653 --> 00:25:21.820
it was probably
"all in my head."

541
00:25:21.822 --> 00:25:25.157
[Scott] <i>Oh</i>
<i>yeah. I know.</i>

542
00:25:25.159 --> 00:25:27.393
I can't release this.

543
00:25:27.395 --> 00:25:29.528
Tyler is going to fire me.

544
00:25:29.530 --> 00:25:32.431
<i>Maybe that's</i>
<i>not so bad.</i>

545
00:25:32.433 --> 00:25:35.868
<i>Maybe you need</i>
<i>a rest. A reset.</i>

546
00:25:35.870 --> 00:25:38.203
Seriously? Seriously. you
think I should let Tyler fire
me?

547
00:25:38.205 --> 00:25:40.572
[Scott] <i>No... no.</i>

548
00:25:40.574 --> 00:25:42.408
<i>But after everything</i>
<i>that's happened</i>

549
00:25:42.410 --> 00:25:44.676
<i>and the whole</i>
<i>Langley thing.</i>

550
00:25:44.678 --> 00:25:45.944
<i>did you ever wonder</i>
<i>if maybe--</i>

551
00:25:45.946 --> 00:25:48.947
My career is
completely destroyed?

552
00:25:48.949 --> 00:25:51.316
<i>Maybe you</i>
<i>need a break.</i>

553
00:25:51.318 --> 00:25:53.652
[sighs]

554
00:25:53.654 --> 00:25:55.554
Why does everyone
keep saying this?

555
00:25:55.556 --> 00:25:57.022
I don't need a break.

556
00:25:57.024 --> 00:25:58.858
I need a story.

557
00:26:00.694 --> 00:26:02.928
I can't hide away like
I did something wrong. Scott.

558
00:26:02.930 --> 00:26:06.598
<i>No. but...</i>
<i>these things take a toll.</i>

559
00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:09.668
<i>I miss you.</i>

560
00:26:09.670 --> 00:26:12.505
<i>I know this isn't fair.</i>
<i>but the article and then--</i>

561
00:26:12.507 --> 00:26:15.307
That Langley article
was important.

562
00:26:15.309 --> 00:26:19.512
-It was the truth.
<i>-Okay. okay.</i>

563
00:26:19.514 --> 00:26:21.647
You know. Langley's cheer
squad is camped outside my flat
now.

564
00:26:21.649 --> 00:26:24.116
<i>What? Jesus.</i>

565
00:26:24.118 --> 00:26:26.753
Yeah. Some hero
must have doxed me.

566
00:26:28.122 --> 00:26:32.024
I've gone back
to Mom and Dad's for a bit.

567
00:26:32.026 --> 00:26:34.393
I thought coming back here
would help.

568
00:26:34.395 --> 00:26:38.031
Some time alone.
find a story. but...

569
00:26:39.433 --> 00:26:42.935
I am stuck.

570
00:26:42.937 --> 00:26:45.404
<i>It's okay to admit</i>
<i>that you're exhausted.</i>

571
00:26:45.406 --> 00:26:48.907
I'm not exhausted.
I am humiliated.

572
00:26:48.909 --> 00:26:51.009
I tried to do the right
thing. and look where it got me.

573
00:26:51.011 --> 00:26:52.978
<i>I know. But...</i>

574
00:26:52.980 --> 00:26:55.814
[Scott sighs]

575
00:26:55.816 --> 00:26:57.717
<i>This kind of work</i>
<i>isn't for everyone.</i>

576
00:27:01.922 --> 00:27:05.057
I've just got to make a
story that will make people
listen.

577
00:27:05.059 --> 00:27:06.793
That is it.

578
00:27:08.329 --> 00:27:09.896
[sighs deeply]

579
00:27:11.765 --> 00:27:14.099
[Floramae] <i>Sometimes. I</i>
<i>think I can still feel it.</i>

580
00:27:14.101 --> 00:27:16.668
<i>that power.</i>

581
00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:21.406
<i>like something</i>
<i>unfinished.</i>

582
00:27:21.408 --> 00:27:24.511
<i>I can't explain it.</i>
<i>I don't know.</i>

583
00:27:24.513 --> 00:27:28.180
<i>This was 20 years</i>
<i>ago. it's silly.</i>

584
00:27:28.182 --> 00:27:31.917
<i>I thought that there</i>
<i>was some kind of power over</i>
<i>me.</i>

585
00:27:31.919 --> 00:27:33.887
<i>Yeah. it was probably</i>
<i>all in my head.</i>

586
00:27:37.758 --> 00:27:39.358
<i>Yeah. it was probably</i>
<i>all in my head.</i>

587
00:27:39.360 --> 00:27:43.162
[tapping at keys]

588
00:27:43.164 --> 00:27:45.697
<i>I can't explain it.</i>

589
00:27:45.699 --> 00:27:48.401
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>this was 20 years a--</i>

590
00:27:49.970 --> 00:27:54.040
[clicking]

591
00:27:57.912 --> 00:28:00.846
<i>Something</i>
<i>unfinished.</i>

592
00:28:00.848 --> 00:28:02.882
<i>Some kind of</i>
<i>power over me.</i>

593
00:28:05.686 --> 00:28:08.820
<i>Something</i>
<i>unfinished.</i>

594
00:28:08.822 --> 00:28:10.689
<i>Some kind of</i>
<i>power over me.</i>

595
00:28:10.691 --> 00:28:13.793
[unsettling music playing]

596
00:28:21.936 --> 00:28:24.369
[interviewer] <i>As I</i>
<i>listen to Floramae and Klaus</i>

597
00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:26.573
<i>describe their</i>
<i>experiences</i>

598
00:28:26.575 --> 00:28:29.775
<i>with these powerful.</i>
<i>dark objects.</i>

599
00:28:29.777 --> 00:28:33.345
<i>I feel a kind of</i>
<i>terror creep over me.</i>

600
00:28:33.347 --> 00:28:35.981
<i>Who sent this</i>
<i>anonymous email</i>

601
00:28:35.983 --> 00:28:37.784
<i>and what do they</i>
<i>want me to find?</i>

602
00:28:39.654 --> 00:28:42.988
<i>Floramae's</i>
<i>words haunt me.</i>

603
00:28:42.990 --> 00:28:45.325
<i>An object filled</i>
<i>with unknowable power.</i>

604
00:28:47.027 --> 00:28:49.028
<i>What do these</i>
<i>bricks want from us?</i>

605
00:28:50.064 --> 00:28:52.731
<i>To solve</i>
<i>this mystery.</i>

606
00:28:52.733 --> 00:28:54.901
<i>I need your</i>
<i>help. listeners.</i>

607
00:28:56.103 --> 00:28:58.737
<i>I wanna know.</i>

608
00:28:58.739 --> 00:29:00.939
<i>is there anyone out</i>
<i>there that knows anything.</i>

609
00:29:00.941 --> 00:29:04.776
<i>anything at all.</i>
<i>about these bricks?</i>

610
00:29:04.778 --> 00:29:09.281
And can we uncover
the dark forces behind them

611
00:29:09.283 --> 00:29:11.083
before it's too late?

612
00:29:11.085 --> 00:29:13.987
[unsettling
music continues]

613
00:29:22.096 --> 00:29:24.831
[clicking]

614
00:29:27.334 --> 00:29:29.268
[whoosh]

615
00:29:29.270 --> 00:29:30.302
[sighs]

616
00:29:30.304 --> 00:29:32.038
Okay.

617
00:29:32.707 --> 00:29:35.208
[sighs deeply]

618
00:29:37.478 --> 00:29:39.278
What do you reckon. Ian?

619
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:42.180
Good idea? Bad idea?

620
00:29:42.182 --> 00:29:43.583
[bubbling]

621
00:29:43.585 --> 00:29:45.551
Undecided. huh?

622
00:29:45.553 --> 00:29:47.053
[notification chime]

623
00:29:49.356 --> 00:29:50.889
[click]

624
00:29:50.891 --> 00:29:54.226
[unsettling music playing]

625
00:29:54.228 --> 00:29:57.096
[sighs]

626
00:29:59.734 --> 00:30:01.668
[clicks]

627
00:30:01.670 --> 00:30:05.071
[somber music playing]

628
00:30:07.609 --> 00:30:11.978
[rapidly
reverberating rhythm]

629
00:30:15.784 --> 00:30:17.784
[whispers]
<i>Happy birthday.</i>

630
00:30:17.786 --> 00:30:20.253
[news anchor speaking
indistinctly over TV]

631
00:30:23.591 --> 00:30:25.291
[notification chimes]

632
00:30:26.060 --> 00:30:28.562
[news continues
indistinctly]

633
00:30:33.367 --> 00:30:35.234
[interviewer gasps]

634
00:30:41.842 --> 00:30:45.010
<i>Are you saying you also</i>
<i>have one of these objects?</i>

635
00:30:45.012 --> 00:30:47.245
[American woman] <i>Yes.</i>
<i>ma'am. I received it two years</i>
<i>ago.</i>

636
00:30:47.247 --> 00:30:49.782
And you don't know
Floramae or Klaus Lang?

637
00:30:49.784 --> 00:30:51.883
<i>Never heard of 'em.</i>

638
00:30:51.885 --> 00:30:54.286
<i>But when I listened</i>
<i>to your podcast.</i>

639
00:30:54.288 --> 00:30:56.656
<i>I thought. "Laura</i>
<i>Sully. that's that damned</i>
<i>rock."</i>

640
00:30:56.658 --> 00:30:58.190
<i>It feels like</i>
<i>I've been waiting years</i>

641
00:30:58.192 --> 00:31:01.059
<i>to talk to</i>
<i>somebody like you.</i>

642
00:31:01.061 --> 00:31:05.097
Okay. then. um...
how did it all start?

643
00:31:05.099 --> 00:31:09.267
<i>A bit over two years</i>
<i>ago. I got ill.</i>

644
00:31:09.269 --> 00:31:10.670
<i>Stopped eating.</i>
<i>Felt like hell.</i>

645
00:31:10.672 --> 00:31:12.605
Did you see a doctor?

646
00:31:12.607 --> 00:31:14.139
<i>Every doctor</i>
<i>in town.</i>

647
00:31:14.141 --> 00:31:16.108
<i>but no amount</i>
<i>of scans</i>

648
00:31:16.110 --> 00:31:17.677
<i>or tests</i>
<i>found a thing.</i>

649
00:31:17.679 --> 00:31:19.579
<i>but...</i>

650
00:31:19.581 --> 00:31:21.279
<i>I can't shake it.</i>

651
00:31:21.281 --> 00:31:24.617
<i>this weight</i>
<i>hanging on me.</i>

652
00:31:24.619 --> 00:31:26.853
<i>It's the visions</i>
<i>that really get me.</i>

653
00:31:26.855 --> 00:31:28.420
You also get visions?

654
00:31:28.422 --> 00:31:30.188
<i>Yes. ma'am.</i>

655
00:31:30.190 --> 00:31:32.324
<i>I call it</i>
<i>hijacking.</i>

656
00:31:32.326 --> 00:31:34.926
<i>It feels violent.</i>
<i>Invasive.</i>

657
00:31:34.928 --> 00:31:38.096
And what do you see?

658
00:31:38.098 --> 00:31:39.766
<i>Well. it's hard to know</i>
<i>exactly when the vision</i>
<i>starts</i>

659
00:31:39.768 --> 00:31:43.770
<i>and reality ends.</i>

660
00:31:43.772 --> 00:31:45.203
<i>It's always</i>
<i>when I'm coming to work.</i>

661
00:31:45.205 --> 00:31:47.973
<i>I'm a financial</i>
<i>consultant.</i>

662
00:31:47.975 --> 00:31:51.544
<i>Work in one of the</i>
<i>tallest buildings in Ohio.</i>

663
00:31:51.546 --> 00:31:56.081
<i>I know I'm having this</i>
<i>vision because there's a</i>
<i>smell.</i>

664
00:31:56.083 --> 00:31:57.817
<i>It's really weird. but</i>
<i>I can really smell it.</i>

665
00:31:57.819 --> 00:31:59.553
What kind of smell?

666
00:32:01.321 --> 00:32:05.323
<i>Um... best way I can</i>
<i>describe it is rotting meat.</i>

667
00:32:05.325 --> 00:32:08.828
<i>like. old. rancid meat</i>
<i>left out in the sun.</i>

668
00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:12.765
[unsettling music playing]

669
00:32:12.767 --> 00:32:14.767
<i>As I walk</i>
<i>through my floor.</i>

670
00:32:14.769 --> 00:32:17.936
<i>I realize the whole</i>
<i>office is empty.</i>

671
00:32:17.938 --> 00:32:20.305
<i>I'm spooked.</i>

672
00:32:20.307 --> 00:32:26.344
<i>It's just silent.</i>
<i>It's deathly silent.</i>

673
00:32:26.346 --> 00:32:29.014
<i>Except for this wind</i>
<i>whistling straight through the</i>
<i>building.</i>

674
00:32:29.016 --> 00:32:32.685
[wind howls]

675
00:32:32.687 --> 00:32:36.354
<i>So I keep walking</i>
<i>straight into my beautiful</i>
<i>office.</i>

676
00:32:36.356 --> 00:32:40.425
<i>View of the city.</i>
<i>all those streets below.</i>

677
00:32:40.427 --> 00:32:43.061
<i>There's a window.</i>
<i>closed tight but still this</i>
<i>wind.</i>

678
00:32:43.063 --> 00:32:46.198
<i>and I know-- don't ask</i>
<i>me how. but I just--</i>

679
00:32:46.200 --> 00:32:49.401
<i>I know the only</i>
<i>thing that could stop</i>

680
00:32:49.403 --> 00:32:51.938
<i>this awful. empty</i>
<i>feeling would be to keep</i>
<i>walking</i>

681
00:32:51.940 --> 00:32:53.906
<i>straight out</i>
<i>that window.</i>

682
00:32:53.908 --> 00:32:56.208
[echoing thud]

683
00:32:56.210 --> 00:32:58.811
<i>So that's</i>
<i>what I do.</i>

684
00:32:58.813 --> 00:32:59.912
<i>And just before</i>
<i>I hit the ground.</i>

685
00:32:59.914 --> 00:33:01.179
<i>I wake up</i>
<i>and I'm at work.</i>

686
00:33:01.181 --> 00:33:03.783
[unsettling
music continues]

687
00:33:03.785 --> 00:33:06.017
<i>And people tell me</i>
<i>that I have been</i>

688
00:33:06.019 --> 00:33:08.320
<i>walking through the</i>
<i>building the whole time.</i>

689
00:33:08.322 --> 00:33:10.422
<i>talking to folks like</i>
<i>there is nothing wrong.</i>

690
00:33:10.424 --> 00:33:12.792
<i>as though none of</i>
<i>it ever happened.</i>

691
00:33:12.794 --> 00:33:16.027
<i>Like I just dreamt</i>
<i>all of it up.</i>

692
00:33:16.029 --> 00:33:18.363
<i>And that's when</i>
<i>I stopped eating.</i>

693
00:33:18.365 --> 00:33:21.433
<i>That's when I received</i>
<i>the black rock.</i>

694
00:33:21.435 --> 00:33:23.302
[interviewer clears
throat] Tell me about it.

695
00:33:25.439 --> 00:33:28.406
<i>This rock ain't like</i>
<i>anything I've ever seen or</i>
<i>felt.</i>

696
00:33:28.408 --> 00:33:32.244
<i>It's more than</i>
<i>just an object.</i>

697
00:33:32.246 --> 00:33:35.781
<i>It wants</i>
<i>something from me.</i>

698
00:33:35.783 --> 00:33:39.050
Do you still have it?

699
00:33:39.052 --> 00:33:42.120
<i>It's sitting</i>
<i>right in front of me.</i>

700
00:33:42.122 --> 00:33:45.858
Could you. uh. could you
send me a photograph of it?

701
00:33:45.860 --> 00:33:47.393
<i>I don't see</i>
<i>why not.</i>

702
00:33:49.129 --> 00:33:51.797
Have you ever tried
to get rid of it?

703
00:33:51.799 --> 00:33:54.366
Destroy it?

704
00:33:54.368 --> 00:33:56.101
<i>Yeah. of course.</i>
<i>I've thought about it.</i>

705
00:33:56.103 --> 00:33:59.070
<i>smashing the thing.</i>

706
00:33:59.072 --> 00:34:01.974
<i>Yeah. Anything</i>
<i>to make it stop.</i>

707
00:34:01.976 --> 00:34:04.276
<i>But then. this...</i>

708
00:34:04.278 --> 00:34:07.648
<i>this feeling</i>
<i>hits me. and...</i>

709
00:34:10.284 --> 00:34:11.216
<i>It's trying</i>
<i>to tell me something</i>

710
00:34:11.218 --> 00:34:13.051
<i>and I gotta listen.</i>

711
00:34:13.053 --> 00:34:15.021
[heartbeat-like
rhythm pulses]

712
00:34:15.023 --> 00:34:18.925
What's it telling you?

713
00:34:18.927 --> 00:34:22.796
<i>Something awful is</i>
<i>coming. truly...</i>

714
00:34:24.832 --> 00:34:27.934
<i>Oh. I'm</i>
<i>sorry. sorry.</i>

715
00:34:27.936 --> 00:34:32.137
<i>I'm sorry. I. uh.</i>
<i>I hope this is helpful.</i>

716
00:34:32.139 --> 00:34:34.072
How did you
find it. Laura?

717
00:34:34.074 --> 00:34:36.474
<i>What do you mean?</i>

718
00:34:36.476 --> 00:34:38.343
Well. you say
you received it.

719
00:34:38.345 --> 00:34:40.345
but how?

720
00:34:40.347 --> 00:34:43.616
Did it just
turn up one day?

721
00:34:43.618 --> 00:34:46.852
Was it in a package
or something?

722
00:34:46.854 --> 00:34:50.088
<i>Uh. look. I--</i>
<i>I can't tell you that.</i>

723
00:34:50.090 --> 00:34:54.426
<i>it was just--</i>
<i>it was there. that's all.</i>

724
00:34:54.428 --> 00:34:56.696
I need you to tell me
everything. Laura. I--

725
00:34:56.698 --> 00:34:59.130
I need to be able
to verify your story.

726
00:34:59.132 --> 00:35:00.098
<i>Uh. you think</i>
<i>I'm making this up?</i>

727
00:35:00.100 --> 00:35:03.168
No. of course not.

728
00:35:03.170 --> 00:35:05.236
But it is important that
I have all the information.

729
00:35:05.238 --> 00:35:08.641
<i>Look. maybe you</i>
<i>can't understand.</i>

730
00:35:08.643 --> 00:35:11.010
<i>but there are some</i>
<i>things that I just can't talk</i>
<i>about.</i>

731
00:35:11.012 --> 00:35:12.713
<i>Simple as that.</i>

732
00:35:14.348 --> 00:35:16.649
You can't or you
won't. Laura?

733
00:35:16.651 --> 00:35:18.985
<i>Look. I-- I have</i>
<i>told you what I can.</i>

734
00:35:18.987 --> 00:35:21.419
<i>Uh. my kids are coming</i>
<i>back from school</i>

735
00:35:21.421 --> 00:35:23.188
<i>and I just gotta go.</i>
<i>so I'm-- I'm sorry...</i>

736
00:35:23.190 --> 00:35:26.157
-No. please. Laura.
<i>-Please!</i>

737
00:35:26.159 --> 00:35:28.360
<i>Please! Please</i>
<i>just help me.</i>

738
00:35:28.362 --> 00:35:29.061
<i>I can't keep living</i>
<i>like this. please!</i>

739
00:35:29.063 --> 00:35:30.863
Laura!

740
00:35:30.865 --> 00:35:33.366
[beeping as call
disconnects]

741
00:35:34.434 --> 00:35:37.403
[bubbling]

742
00:35:38.940 --> 00:35:41.273
[printer clicking
and whirring]

743
00:35:53.387 --> 00:35:55.688
<i>This is</i>
<i>Floramae King.</i>

744
00:35:55.690 --> 00:35:58.524
<i>My daughter Paula just</i>
<i>played me your podcast.</i>

745
00:35:58.526 --> 00:36:01.627
<i>You changed my words</i>
<i>around. and I...</i>

746
00:36:01.629 --> 00:36:04.830
<i>I don't want that</i>
<i>family to hear me say those</i>
<i>things.</i>

747
00:36:04.832 --> 00:36:07.399
<i>-They were so angry</i>
<i>last time.</i> -[man 1] <i>My</i>
<i>friend refuses</i>

748
00:36:07.401 --> 00:36:10.468
<i>to tell me where it</i>
<i>came from. like he is</i>
<i>scared.</i>

749
00:36:10.470 --> 00:36:13.506
[woman 1] <i>The last we</i>
<i>heard was she's in a secure</i>
<i>facility.</i>

750
00:36:13.508 --> 00:36:15.775
[man 2] <i>Aliens are</i>
<i>comin'. and they want to</i>
<i>destroy...</i>

751
00:36:15.777 --> 00:36:17.743
[woman 2] <i>Eight months</i>
<i>after. we received this black</i>
<i>rock.</i>

752
00:36:17.745 --> 00:36:19.210
<i>The operations manager</i>
<i>in Dubai received one...</i>

753
00:36:19.212 --> 00:36:20.880
[man 3] <i>My father</i>
<i>believed the stone</i>

754
00:36:20.882 --> 00:36:22.247
<i>was an omen sent</i>
<i>from the dead.</i>

755
00:36:22.249 --> 00:36:24.850
<i>He won't tell me</i>
<i>how he got it.</i>

756
00:36:24.852 --> 00:36:26.519
[woman 3] <i>We are all</i>
<i>scared that we will get one</i>
<i>next.</i>

757
00:36:26.521 --> 00:36:30.089
<i>But why? What is this</i>
<i>rock? What does it want?</i>

758
00:36:30.091 --> 00:36:33.125
[man 2] <i>Every</i>
<i>civilization has an end. and</i>
<i>this is ours!</i>

759
00:36:33.127 --> 00:36:35.127
[man 2]
<i>Are you listening to me?</i>

760
00:36:35.129 --> 00:36:39.699
[montage of voices
and email notifications]

761
00:36:39.701 --> 00:36:42.601
[man 4] <i>You have to</i>
<i>stop this podcast!</i>

762
00:36:42.603 --> 00:36:44.537
[interviewer] <i>When did</i>
<i>your grandfather receive the</i>
<i>brick?</i>

763
00:36:44.539 --> 00:36:46.605
[man 4] <i>You're making</i>
<i>it worse. The brick is</i>
<i>spreading.</i>

764
00:36:46.607 --> 00:36:48.440
<i>We shouldn't be</i>
<i>talking about this.</i>

765
00:36:48.442 --> 00:36:51.276
[interviewer] <i>Just a</i>
<i>couple more minutes.</i>

766
00:36:51.278 --> 00:36:55.213
<i>Did your grandfather</i>
<i>ever tell you how he received</i>
<i>it</i>

767
00:36:55.215 --> 00:36:58.150
<i>or if someone</i>
<i>gave it to him?</i>

768
00:36:58.152 --> 00:37:00.920
[man 4] <i>He refused.</i>

769
00:37:00.922 --> 00:37:04.222
<i>He said we wouldn't</i>
<i>believe it. That he was</i>
<i>ashamed.</i>

770
00:37:04.224 --> 00:37:07.560
<i>Other people talk</i>
<i>about getting visions.</i>

771
00:37:07.562 --> 00:37:11.229
<i>Has your grandfather</i>
<i>ever experienced anything like</i>
<i>that?</i>

772
00:37:11.231 --> 00:37:13.966
<i>I told him</i>
<i>I wouldn't tell anyone.</i>

773
00:37:13.968 --> 00:37:16.267
<i>I only called</i>
<i>to warn you!</i>

774
00:37:16.269 --> 00:37:19.370
I'm trying to understand
what these bricks are.

775
00:37:19.372 --> 00:37:22.709
but you have to tell me
what has happened.

776
00:37:25.245 --> 00:37:27.613
Let me help you.

777
00:37:27.615 --> 00:37:30.116
We can speak
off the record.

778
00:37:30.118 --> 00:37:32.317
[faint traffic sounds]

779
00:37:32.319 --> 00:37:33.987
<i>You won't</i>
<i>record us?</i>

780
00:37:35.890 --> 00:37:37.657
I won't record us.

781
00:37:39.193 --> 00:37:42.528
<i>Okay... okay.</i>

782
00:37:42.530 --> 00:37:45.330
<i>We can talk.</i>
<i>but not for long.</i>

783
00:37:45.332 --> 00:37:49.602
[man breathing shakily]

784
00:37:49.604 --> 00:37:54.807
<i>My grandfather has been</i>
<i>having these visions. yes?</i>

785
00:37:54.809 --> 00:37:57.308
[unsettling music playing]

786
00:37:57.310 --> 00:37:59.512
<i>Many years ago.</i>

787
00:37:59.514 --> 00:38:02.047
<i>my grandfather</i>
<i>had an affair</i>

788
00:38:02.049 --> 00:38:05.017
<i>and fathered a son</i>
<i>with another woman.</i>

789
00:38:05.019 --> 00:38:07.052
<i>We never knew.</i>

790
00:38:07.054 --> 00:38:09.755
<i>Years later.</i>

791
00:38:09.757 --> 00:38:13.559
<i>he sees this woman</i>
<i>at a shopping mall.</i>

792
00:38:13.561 --> 00:38:18.931
<i>She has her son.</i>
<i>his son. with her.</i>

793
00:38:18.933 --> 00:38:22.035
<i>But the boy looks at</i>
<i>him like a stranger.</i>

794
00:38:23.905 --> 00:38:25.571
<i>He never saw</i>
<i>them again.</i>

795
00:38:25.573 --> 00:38:29.208
[unsettling
music continues]

796
00:38:29.210 --> 00:38:32.410
<i>One night a</i>
<i>few months ago.</i>

797
00:38:32.412 --> 00:38:36.715
<i>I found my grandfather</i>
<i>in the dining room alone.</i>

798
00:38:36.717 --> 00:38:41.954
<i>I have never seen him</i>
<i>look so frightened.</i>

799
00:38:41.956 --> 00:38:44.723
<i>He was whispering to</i>
<i>an empty chair. saying.</i>

800
00:38:44.725 --> 00:38:50.496
<i>"I am sorry. I am</i>
<i>sorry." over and over again.</i>

801
00:38:51.833 --> 00:38:55.768
<i>He told me that for</i>
<i>weeks. every night.</i>

802
00:38:55.770 --> 00:38:59.805
<i>a young boy had sat</i>
<i>eating dinner with us.</i>

803
00:38:59.807 --> 00:39:02.474
<i>Only my grandfather</i>
<i>could see him.</i>

804
00:39:04.312 --> 00:39:07.514
<i>He believed it was</i>
<i>his son haunting him.</i>

805
00:39:10.852 --> 00:39:14.887
<i>A few weeks ago.</i>
<i>the boy stopped coming.</i>

806
00:39:14.889 --> 00:39:17.590
<i>The brick is gone.</i>

807
00:39:17.592 --> 00:39:22.863
<i>But my grandfather</i>
<i>has changed.</i>

808
00:39:25.132 --> 00:39:31.571
<i>Like he has been</i>
<i>replaced with something</i>
<i>else.</i>

809
00:39:35.810 --> 00:39:37.576
[man] <i>Hello?</i>

810
00:39:37.578 --> 00:39:39.111
<i>Are you</i>
<i>there? Hello?</i>

811
00:39:39.113 --> 00:39:41.748
Um...yes. sorry.

812
00:39:43.784 --> 00:39:46.151
You said your
grandfather's brick has
disappeared.

813
00:39:46.153 --> 00:39:48.453
<i>I told you.</i>
<i>it's gone.</i>

814
00:39:48.455 --> 00:39:51.257
<i>And ever since.</i>
<i>he's different.</i>

815
00:39:51.259 --> 00:39:52.758
-[man sighs heavily]
-Different how?

816
00:39:52.760 --> 00:39:55.493
<i>There's nothing</i>
<i>behind his eyes.</i>

817
00:39:55.495 --> 00:39:58.864
<i>-No soul.</i>
-Right.

818
00:39:58.866 --> 00:40:01.432
<i>And now. my father</i>
<i>has been getting sick.</i>

819
00:40:01.434 --> 00:40:03.335
<i>The same sick</i>
<i>as my grandfather.</i>

820
00:40:03.337 --> 00:40:05.671
<i>He won't eat.</i>
<i>Can't work.</i>

821
00:40:05.673 --> 00:40:07.373
<i>I'm so scared</i>
<i>he's going to receive</i>

822
00:40:07.375 --> 00:40:09.975
<i>this object</i>
<i>as well.</i>

823
00:40:09.977 --> 00:40:12.044
Is he also
getting visions?

824
00:40:12.046 --> 00:40:14.179
<i>Yes. He is</i>
<i>terrified.</i>

825
00:40:14.181 --> 00:40:15.347
<i>He knows what</i>
<i>is coming.</i>

826
00:40:15.349 --> 00:40:17.316
<i>I could be next.</i>

827
