trying to spook me
for some reason.

1041
00:54:11.819 --> 00:54:13.284
<i>I don't know what</i>
<i>you're talking about.</i>

1042
00:54:13.286 --> 00:54:15.487
<i>A symbol? You</i>
<i>have a brick?</i>

1043
00:54:15.489 --> 00:54:16.922
You can't do this to me.

1044
00:54:16.924 --> 00:54:20.358
I will call the cops.

1045
00:54:20.360 --> 00:54:22.895
-I will ruin your gallery.
<i>-I'm doing nothing.</i>

1046
00:54:22.897 --> 00:54:25.765
<i>I'm at the playground</i>
<i>with my grandchildren.</i>

1047
00:54:25.767 --> 00:54:28.200
<i>Please listen. I really</i>
<i>don't know what you're talking</i>
<i>about.</i>

1048
00:54:28.202 --> 00:54:29.602
<i>I'm telling</i>
<i>you the truth.</i>

1049
00:54:29.604 --> 00:54:31.671
<i>I have no reason</i>
<i>to lie to you.</i>

1050
00:54:34.776 --> 00:54:37.408
<i>You're starting to</i>
<i>think this Klaus character</i>

1051
00:54:37.410 --> 00:54:39.545
<i>not so crazy. huh?</i>

1052
00:54:39.547 --> 00:54:40.880
Be straight with me.
Are these bricks real?

1053
00:54:40.882 --> 00:54:42.883
<i>Yes.</i>

1054
00:54:45.620 --> 00:54:49.454
How do you know
if you're having these visions?

1055
00:54:49.456 --> 00:54:51.322
<i>The bricks have really</i>
<i>got under your skin.</i>

1056
00:54:51.324 --> 00:54:53.492
<i>haven't they?</i>

1057
00:54:55.163 --> 00:54:56.829
<i>You ask</i>
<i>what is the difference</i>

1058
00:54:56.831 --> 00:55:00.132
<i>between these</i>
<i>visions and reality.</i>

1059
00:55:00.134 --> 00:55:03.235
<i>I really</i>
<i>don't know.</i>

1060
00:55:03.237 --> 00:55:05.938
<i>Depending on which</i>
<i>way you look at it.</i>

1061
00:55:05.940 --> 00:55:08.707
<i>perhaps nothing.</i>

1062
00:55:08.709 --> 00:55:12.646
Klaus. I want you
to show me the brick.

1063
00:55:14.347 --> 00:55:16.649
Prove to me they're real.

1064
00:55:16.651 --> 00:55:18.818
<i>Okay. Tomorrow.</i>
<i>I can go to my--</i>

1065
00:55:18.820 --> 00:55:22.621
No. Not tomorrow. now.

1066
00:55:22.623 --> 00:55:24.523
<i>I told you.</i>
<i>I'm at a playground.</i>

1067
00:55:24.525 --> 00:55:25.658
<i>My granddaughter</i>
<i>just--</i>

1068
00:55:25.660 --> 00:55:27.726
I'm sure the authorities
would be interested

1069
00:55:27.728 --> 00:55:29.595
in checking
the provenance certificates

1070
00:55:29.597 --> 00:55:31.897
of the artwork you sell.

1071
00:55:31.899 --> 00:55:34.266
I can make the call

1072
00:55:34.268 --> 00:55:37.368
and see just how
interested they might be.

1073
00:55:37.370 --> 00:55:37.970
<i>Are you</i>
<i>threatening me?</i>

1074
00:55:37.972 --> 00:55:40.073
Yes. I am.

1075
00:55:46.147 --> 00:55:48.380
You just have to help me.
Klaus. please.

1076
00:55:50.417 --> 00:55:52.417
<i>Give me 30 minutes.</i>

1077
00:55:52.419 --> 00:55:54.020
[phone beeps]

1078
00:55:57.625 --> 00:56:00.459
[wind howling softly]

1079
00:56:09.971 --> 00:56:11.705
[beep]

1080
00:56:16.878 --> 00:56:18.244
Hello?

1081
00:56:18.246 --> 00:56:21.412
[wind howling softly]

1082
00:56:21.414 --> 00:56:24.450
If anyone's out there.
I'm not scared.

1083
00:56:33.426 --> 00:56:36.129
[microwave humming]

1084
00:56:40.902 --> 00:56:42.067
[microwave beeping]

1085
00:56:42.069 --> 00:56:44.970
[vomiting]

1086
00:56:44.972 --> 00:56:46.138
[spits]

1087
00:56:46.140 --> 00:56:47.908
[coughs]

1088
00:56:49.076 --> 00:56:52.144
[water running]

1089
00:56:52.146 --> 00:56:55.381
[unsettling music playing]

1090
00:56:55.383 --> 00:56:57.449
[breathing shakily] Eat.

1091
00:56:58.519 --> 00:57:01.486
Eat. Come on. Ian.

1092
00:57:01.488 --> 00:57:04.123
[sighs] What is wrong with
you. stupid turtle?

1093
00:57:04.125 --> 00:57:06.759
[filter bubbling]

1094
00:57:06.761 --> 00:57:11.096
[unsettling
music continues]

1095
00:57:11.098 --> 00:57:13.532
[sighs]

1096
00:57:13.534 --> 00:57:16.435
[cell phone ringing]

1097
00:57:18.940 --> 00:57:21.472
Klaus. what the fuck
took you so long?

1098
00:57:21.474 --> 00:57:24.643
[Klaus] <i>I'm here</i>
<i>in my vault.</i>

1099
00:57:24.645 --> 00:57:26.312
-Just wait.
<i>-I haven't</i>

1100
00:57:26.314 --> 00:57:27.780
<i>seen the brick</i>
<i>for so long.</i>

1101
00:57:27.782 --> 00:57:28.881
<i>but it looks</i>
<i>how I remember.</i>

1102
00:57:28.883 --> 00:57:31.350
Hold on. I need
to record this.

1103
00:57:31.352 --> 00:57:35.354
<i>After all these years.</i>
<i>it feels the same.</i>

1104
00:57:35.356 --> 00:57:37.222
<i>That awful feeling.</i>

1105
00:57:37.224 --> 00:57:38.624
You said you had
a few bricks.

1106
00:57:38.626 --> 00:57:41.226
You've got--
you've got dozens.

1107
00:57:41.228 --> 00:57:43.729
<i>I spent my life</i>
<i>collecting. trying to</i>
<i>understand.</i>

1108
00:57:43.731 --> 00:57:45.832
<i>but none of it</i>
<i>matters now.</i>

1109
00:57:47.368 --> 00:57:48.534
<i>My brother is here.</i>

1110
00:57:48.536 --> 00:57:51.370
[groaning]

1111
00:57:51.372 --> 00:57:53.105
What?

1112
00:57:53.107 --> 00:57:54.406
You can see him?

1113
00:57:54.408 --> 00:57:56.942
<i>I can sense him.</i>

1114
00:57:56.944 --> 00:57:59.645
<i>He's here.</i>

1115
00:57:59.647 --> 00:58:03.349
<i>And this sound. all I</i>
<i>can hear is this sound.</i>

1116
00:58:03.351 --> 00:58:04.650
[groaning]

1117
00:58:04.652 --> 00:58:06.919
Klaus. I can't see.

1118
00:58:06.921 --> 00:58:09.855
You need to show me
what is happening.

1119
00:58:09.857 --> 00:58:12.658
<i>Please. stop.</i>
<i>stop. stop!</i>

1120
00:58:12.660 --> 00:58:14.927
What are you doing?

1121
00:58:14.929 --> 00:58:17.129
<i>It has to end.</i>
<i>Yes. it must.</i>

1122
00:58:17.131 --> 00:58:18.931
Klaus. can--
can you hear me?

1123
00:58:18.933 --> 00:58:21.133
Pick up the phone.

1124
00:58:21.135 --> 00:58:24.938
[groaning. thudding]

1125
00:58:31.078 --> 00:58:32.678
[groans]

1126
00:58:32.680 --> 00:58:35.881
[unsettling
music continues]

1127
00:58:35.883 --> 00:58:36.849
[groaning]

1128
00:58:36.851 --> 00:58:38.417
Klaus.

1129
00:58:38.419 --> 00:58:40.120
<i>There's nothing...</i>

1130
00:58:41.789 --> 00:58:43.622
[bubbling. squelching]

1131
00:58:43.624 --> 00:58:45.824
<i>Oh my god.</i>

1132
00:58:45.826 --> 00:58:48.193
[rustling]

1133
00:58:48.195 --> 00:58:50.329
[phone beeps]

1134
00:58:50.331 --> 00:58:52.364
Fuck.

1135
00:58:52.366 --> 00:58:54.266
[audible breathing]

1136
00:58:54.268 --> 00:58:57.436
[phone ringing]

1137
00:58:57.438 --> 00:58:58.303
[female voice] <i>The</i>
<i>number you have dialed</i>

1138
00:58:58.305 --> 00:59:00.472
<i>is currently</i>
<i>unavailable.</i>

1139
00:59:00.474 --> 00:59:04.076
<i>Please leave a</i>
<i>message and try again.</i>

1140
00:59:04.078 --> 00:59:06.845
<i>The number you have</i>
<i>dialed is currently</i>
<i>unavailable.</i>

1141
00:59:06.847 --> 00:59:08.247
<i>Please leave a</i>
<i>message and try again.</i>

1142
00:59:08.249 --> 00:59:11.450
[audible breathing]

1143
00:59:11.452 --> 00:59:15.054
<i>I can sense</i>
<i>him. He's here.</i>

1144
00:59:15.056 --> 00:59:18.090
<i>And this sound. all I</i>
<i>can hear is this sound.</i>

1145
00:59:18.092 --> 00:59:19.792
<i>Welcome to Beyond</i>
<i>Believable.</i>

1146
00:59:19.794 --> 00:59:22.594
[overlapping chatter]

1147
00:59:22.596 --> 00:59:25.064
<i>I believe my life</i>
<i>is in danger.</i>

1148
00:59:25.066 --> 00:59:27.933
[woman] <i>But why? What</i>
<i>is this rock? What does it</i>
<i>want?</i>

1149
00:59:27.935 --> 00:59:29.802
[Klaus] <i>Trying to</i>
<i>understand. but none of that</i>
<i>matters now.</i>

1150
00:59:29.804 --> 00:59:30.969
[man] <i>Are you</i>
<i>listening to me?</i>

1151
00:59:30.971 --> 00:59:32.404
[interviewer]
<i>What happened...</i>

1152
00:59:32.406 --> 00:59:34.406
<i>in Klaus Lang's</i>
<i>art vault?</i>

1153
00:59:34.408 --> 00:59:35.808
[man] <i>Every</i>
<i>civilization has...</i>

1154
00:59:35.810 --> 00:59:37.943
<i>Thank you.</i>
<i>thank you!</i>

1155
00:59:37.945 --> 00:59:39.445
<i>And was I the last</i>
<i>person to speak to him</i>
<i>alive?</i>

1156
00:59:39.447 --> 00:59:42.414
[man] <i>For</i>
<i>fuck's sake.</i>

1157
00:59:42.416 --> 00:59:44.049
[Scott] <i>But it feels</i>
<i>untethered from any language I</i>
<i>know of.</i>

1158
00:59:44.051 --> 00:59:46.285
[man] <i>I only called</i>
<i>to warn you.</i>

1159
00:59:46.287 --> 00:59:47.419
[woman] <i>Unlike anything</i>
<i>I've ever seen before.</i>

1160
00:59:47.421 --> 00:59:49.655
[overlapping chatter]

1161
00:59:49.657 --> 00:59:52.291
I have to continue
this podcast.

1162
00:59:52.293 --> 00:59:54.460
I have to find the truth.

1163
00:59:54.462 --> 00:59:57.396
[Klaus] <i>All I can</i>
<i>hear is this sound.</i>

1164
00:59:57.398 --> 01:00:01.733
[man] <i>But my</i>
<i>grandfather has changed.</i>

1165
01:00:01.735 --> 01:00:04.670
<i>Something terrible</i>
<i>is coming.</i>

1166
01:00:04.672 --> 01:00:06.605
<i>Something...</i>

1167
01:00:06.607 --> 01:00:08.073
[woman]
<i>But it was me it chose.</i>

1168
01:00:08.075 --> 01:00:10.543
<i>...unbelievable.</i>

1169
01:00:10.545 --> 01:00:15.380
[Beyond Believable
theme music playing]

1170
01:00:15.382 --> 01:00:18.084
[cell phone ringing]

1171
01:00:18.986 --> 01:00:20.753
[sighs]

1172
01:00:21.122 --> 01:00:22.855
Dad?

1173
01:00:22.857 --> 01:00:24.591
[woman] <i>Ah.</i>
<i>sorry. no.</i>

1174
01:00:24.593 --> 01:00:25.558
<i>Is it too early?</i>

1175
01:00:25.560 --> 01:00:27.092
Who is this?

1176
01:00:27.094 --> 01:00:28.828
<i>Shiloh Lowden.</i>

1177
01:00:30.965 --> 01:00:32.532
<i>You wanted to chat</i>
<i>about my article from yonks</i>
<i>ago.</i>

1178
01:00:32.534 --> 01:00:34.867
Yeah. um...
[clears throat]

1179
01:00:34.869 --> 01:00:36.503
Yeah. thank you. uh.
for calling me back.

1180
01:00:36.505 --> 01:00:39.271
Um...

1181
01:00:39.273 --> 01:00:42.474
Sorry. I've just had
a pretty weird couple of days.

1182
01:00:42.476 --> 01:00:44.910
<i>I can imagine.</i>

1183
01:00:44.912 --> 01:00:46.546
<i>I listened</i>
<i>to your last episode.</i>

1184
01:00:46.548 --> 01:00:48.748
You listen to my podcast?

1185
01:00:49.650 --> 01:00:51.483
<i>I did my research.</i>

1186
01:00:51.485 --> 01:00:52.484
Yeah. um...

1187
01:00:52.486 --> 01:00:53.385
[clears throat]

1188
01:00:53.387 --> 01:00:55.154
Right.

1189
01:00:55.156 --> 01:00:57.890
Then you would know
that I think

1190
01:00:57.892 --> 01:01:00.926
what you wrote
back in 1988

1191
01:01:00.928 --> 01:01:04.531
and what I'm investigating
are the same thing.

1192
01:01:04.533 --> 01:01:09.434
Uh. I'm trying to find
patterns to understand what's
happening.

1193
01:01:09.436 --> 01:01:10.570
and I need to know
what you know.

1194
01:01:10.572 --> 01:01:13.005
<i>Right.</i>

1195
01:01:13.007 --> 01:01:15.307
And I thought as a more
experienced journalist.

1196
01:01:15.309 --> 01:01:18.944
you would be prepared
to share with me.

1197
01:01:18.946 --> 01:01:20.647
<i>I'm not certain I know</i>
<i>much that will help you.</i>

1198
01:01:20.649 --> 01:01:22.881
<i>but I'm happy</i>
<i>to share.</i>

1199
01:01:22.883 --> 01:01:28.887
Great. Uh. please tell me
about the article.

1200
01:01:28.889 --> 01:01:31.558
<i>Well. back when I was</i>
<i>working at the Chronicle.</i>

1201
01:01:31.560 --> 01:01:33.325
<i>I had a mate who worked</i>
<i>in a hush-hush research</i>
<i>department</i>

1202
01:01:33.327 --> 01:01:35.595
<i>at Oxford.</i>
<i>government-funded.</i>

1203
01:01:35.597 --> 01:01:38.096
<i>something about</i>
<i>international threats.</i>
<i>terrorism.</i>

1204
01:01:38.098 --> 01:01:39.798
<i>I mean. this is back in</i>
<i>the days of Russia. Reagan.</i>

1205
01:01:39.800 --> 01:01:42.234
<i>the decline</i>
<i>of the West.</i>

1206
01:01:42.236 --> 01:01:45.237
<i>My paper would kill</i>
<i>for any Cold War scoop.</i>

1207
01:01:45.239 --> 01:01:47.139
<i>So we're out drinking</i>
<i>and I get him to tell me</i>

1208
01:01:47.141 --> 01:01:48.740
<i>about a study</i>
<i>his team is doing</i>

1209
01:01:48.742 --> 01:01:50.943
<i>into this</i>
<i>neurological illness</i>

1210
01:01:50.945 --> 01:01:52.778
<i>that had been detected</i>
<i>around the world.</i>

1211
01:01:52.780 --> 01:01:56.081
<i>accompanied by these</i>
<i>unexplained objects.</i>

1212
01:01:56.083 --> 01:01:58.984
What did they suspect
the objects were at the time?

1213
01:01:58.986 --> 01:02:00.452
<i>The department</i>
<i>had convinced themselves</i>

1214
01:02:00.454 --> 01:02:02.421
<i>it was the</i>
<i>Russians.</i>

1215
01:02:02.423 --> 01:02:03.922
<i>absolutely besotted</i>
<i>with the idea.</i>

1216
01:02:03.924 --> 01:02:06.191
But you didn't think so?

1217
01:02:06.193 --> 01:02:07.993
<i>My mate fed me</i>
<i>a departmental memo</i>

1218
01:02:07.995 --> 01:02:09.995
<i>on the sly.</i>
<i>and when I read it.</i>

1219
01:02:09.997 --> 01:02:11.296
<i>I mean. it seemed</i>
<i>completely bonkers.</i>

1220
01:02:11.298 --> 01:02:13.566
Why?

1221
01:02:13.568 --> 01:02:15.734
<i>Well. the study</i>
<i>claimed that 70%</i>

1222
01:02:15.736 --> 01:02:17.704
<i>of the affected people</i>
<i>only developed symptoms</i>

1223
01:02:17.706 --> 01:02:19.539
<i>after hearing</i>
<i>about this object.</i>

1224
01:02:19.541 --> 01:02:22.140
<i>whatever it was.</i>
<i>from someone else.</i>

1225
01:02:22.142 --> 01:02:24.977
You're talking
about a disease spreading

1226
01:02:24.979 --> 01:02:27.746
through people
talking about it?

1227
01:02:27.748 --> 01:02:29.649
<i>It was the main line</i>
<i>of investigation</i>

1228
01:02:29.651 --> 01:02:31.950
<i>the government</i>
<i>was pursuing at the time.</i>

1229
01:02:31.952 --> 01:02:35.220
<i>a kind of viral disease</i>
<i>that traveled through sound.</i>

1230
01:02:35.222 --> 01:02:37.289
<i>Now I know the Russians</i>
<i>had a lot of tools</i>

1231
01:02:37.291 --> 01:02:38.625
<i>at their disposal. but</i>
<i>I don't think even they</i>

1232
01:02:38.627 --> 01:02:39.992
<i>were capable</i>
<i>of that.</i>

1233
01:02:39.994 --> 01:02:41.960
Do you still
have this memo?

1234
01:02:41.962 --> 01:02:45.130
<i>Sadly. long lost.</i>

1235
01:02:45.132 --> 01:02:48.100
What about your friend.
the department source?

1236
01:02:48.102 --> 01:02:50.168
<i>Posted to some</i>
<i>faraway place.</i>

1237
01:02:50.170 --> 01:02:51.970
<i>But...</i>

1238
01:02:51.972 --> 01:02:54.540
<i>I did hear</i>
<i>he got sick.</i>

1239
01:02:54.542 --> 01:02:56.643
The same sort of sickness.

1240
01:02:56.645 --> 01:02:58.443
[unsettling music playing]

1241
01:02:58.445 --> 01:03:00.280
<i>We lost touch.</i>

1242
01:03:01.683 --> 01:03:03.750
Did you ever
form an opinion

1243
01:03:03.752 --> 01:03:08.420
about this illness
and these objects?

1244
01:03:08.422 --> 01:03:12.190
<i>To be honest. I didn't</i>
<i>think much of it back then.</i>

1245
01:03:12.192 --> 01:03:15.628
<i>Government jumping</i>
<i>at shadows.</i>

1246
01:03:15.630 --> 01:03:19.699
<i>But now I've listened</i>
<i>to your podcast.</i>

1247
01:03:19.701 --> 01:03:22.735
<i>it's clearly</i>
<i>compelling stuff.</i>

1248
01:03:22.737 --> 01:03:23.935
<i>But if my article</i>
<i>and your story</i>

1249
01:03:23.937 --> 01:03:26.438
<i>are the same thing.</i>

1250
01:03:26.440 --> 01:03:28.708
<i>you need to</i>
<i>be careful.</i>

1251
01:03:28.710 --> 01:03:31.310
What do you mean?

1252
01:03:31.312 --> 01:03:34.112
<i>We have a duty</i>
<i>to protect the public.</i>

1253
01:03:34.114 --> 01:03:36.848
[unsettling
music continues]

1254
01:03:36.850 --> 01:03:38.851
<i>Not everything</i>
<i>needs to be published.</i>

1255
01:03:40.689 --> 01:03:43.288
Of course.

1256
01:03:43.290 --> 01:03:44.890
Thank you so much
for your time.

1257
01:03:44.892 --> 01:03:46.626
I think I've got
everything I need.

1258
